rComments: Great professor! Learned a lot in his class. It was challenging, but really rewarding.
Remy made this class more engaging by constantly thinking of ways to encourage participation from those of us who are shy/lazy. I appreciated that.

I really improved because he teaches only in Spanish, but answers questions in Englis or French. I didn't like the book though, but it's the one they use for all the classes because it's 100% in Spanish, I don't think he picked it. Also, attendance counts.

My Spanish really improved by taking this class, and I thought the whole thing was probably one of the easiest courses I've ever took. There's very little work to do. He's also young and extremely good looking, so that's always a plus.  However, the classes were very boring (mostly due to the material).
